cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.AI. 

The paper presents a technique for improving greybox fuzzing, which is a software testing approach. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also focuses on detecting bugs and security vulnerabilities, which suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as another likely category. The technique involves learning new inputs based on already explored program executions, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the technique uses machine learning to guide exploration, which could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
